article.description: Earl Potts Jr. scored 20 points with nine rebounds and Fairleigh Dickinson edged Mount St. Mary's 80-75 on Saturday in a Northeast Conference tournament semifinal game.
article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson tops Mount St. Mary's 80-75 in NEC
article.linkText: Fairleigh Dickinson tops Mount St. Mary's 80-75 in NEC
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- Earl Potts Jr. scored 20 points with nine rebounds and Fairleigh Dickinson edged Mount St. Mary's 80-75 on Saturday in a Northeast Conference tournament semifinal game. The Knights (17-14) advance to play top-seeded Wagner (22-9), winners over LIU Brooklyn, in the championship game on Tuesday. A close game throughout, FDU took a one-point lead with 4:33 to go on Potts' 3-pointer. Darnell Edge's triple a minute later made it a six-point contest. The Mount got it back to two after a pair of free throws by Junior Robinson with 1:25 left, but Potts hit another 3 the next time down and the Knights held on to advance. Mike Holloway scored 19 points with 17 rebounds -- a career high for the freshman -- for FDU. Darian Anderson scored 14 points and Stephan Jiggetts added 12. Mount St. Mary's (14-19) was led by Robinson with 21 points. Chris Wray scored 12 points while Gregory Graves and Charles Glover both finished with 10.
